# ============================================================
# Supabase Self-Hosted Configuration
# ============================================================
# After running `docker compose up -d` from the supabase/ directory,
# the Supabase services will be available at:
#
#   Studio (Dashboard):  http://your-server:8000
#   API (Anon/Public):   http://your-server:8000
#   PostgreSQL:          postgresql://postgres:your_password@your-server:5432/postgres
#
# Get these values from the Supabase Studio dashboard after first launch:
#   Project Settings → API → Project URL + anon/public key
# ============================================================

SUPABASE_URL=http://your-server:8000
SUPABASE_ANON_KEY=your-anon-key-from-studio-dashboard
